@NODE INTRO "Introduction"

@{b}@{fg shine}Introduction@{ub}@{fg filltext}
BaseConvert lets you:-
Input 2 numbers in (Decimal 100),  (Hexdecimal &ff), (Binary %1010) 
then you can: Add, Sub, And, Or, Xor, Shift <<, Shift >> them.
and show the result in (Dec, Hex, Bin).

You can copy the result string (Ctrl C) to clipboard and paste (Ctrl V) to
any program that lets you paste from the clipboard, this includes ReAction string
gadgets.

Gadget help is shown in the window title bar.

@ENDNODE

@NODE INSTALL "Installation"

@{b}@{fg shine}Installation@{ub}@{fg filltext}

Copy: @{b}BaseConvert to where you want to on your hard drive.@{ub},


That's it....

@ENDNODE

@NODE REQUIRE "Requirements"

@{b}@{fg shine}Requirements@{ub}@{fg filltext}

0.. Amiga with a 68020/30/40/60 processor.

o.. Workbench 3.5/9. I use the ReAction Classes for the GUI.

@ENDNODE

@NODE TEST "Tested On"

@{b}@{fg shine}Tested On@{ub}@{fg filltext}

o.. A1200, WB3.9, Blizzard 68060+SCSI+130Mb Ram, SCSI HD & 40xCD-ROM.
o.. A1200, WB3.9, Blizzard 68030+SCSI+26Mb Ram, SCSI 12xCD-ROM.

@ENDNODE

@NODE USAGE "How to Use BaseConvert"

@{b}@{fg shine}How to Use BaseConvert@{ub}@{fg filltext}

The program is very simple to use.


o.. Enter a number into the Input string gadget.
    
o.. Enter a number into the Operator string gadget.
    
o.. Seclect the Operator (Add, Sub, And, Or, Xor, Shift <<, Shift >>)

o.. The resut is shown in the Result string gadget.

o.. Change the base using the RadioButton gadget.
    

Changing any of the gadgets automaticlly changes the Result.

@{b}@{fg shine}Menus@{ub}@{fg filltext}


About ...................(Amiga A).

Iconify..................(Amiga I).

Quit.....................(Amiga Q).

@{b}@{fg shine}Keys@{ub}@{fg filltext}

Esc     Quit.

@ENDNODE

